The data layout in memory (after 'first'):

    Offset 0:  77   ← 'first'
    Offset 8:  99   ← 'second'

    adr x1, first      // x1 points to offset 0 (where 77 lives)
    ldr x0, [x1, #8]   // loads offset 8 = 99   ✗ (wrong!)
    ldr x0, [x1]       // loads offset 0 = 77   ✓

To load from the base address without any offset, use just [x1]:
    ldr x0, [x1]

This is equivalent to [x1, #0].
